t when it's being run by an agent (not a human) and skip interactive prompts.\\n\\nLooking at the code again:\\n1. `hasTTY()` checks if /dev/tty can be opened\\n2. If there's no TTY, the fast path kicks in for agent commits\\n3. But when Gemini runs, there IS a TTY (from the user's terminal), so the fast path is skipped\\n4. Then for `source=\\\"message\\\"`, it tries to ask interactively\\n\\nThe issue is that `hasTTY()` returns true when Gemini is running because Gemini inherits the user's terminal. But Gemini can't actually respond to TTY prompts.\\n\\nThe real fix should be to detect that an agent session is ACTIVE and skip interactive prompts in that case, regardless of TTY availability. The code already has this logic but it's gated behind `!hasTTY()`:\\n\\n```go\\n// Fast path: when an agent is committing (ACTIVE session + no TTY), skip\\nif !hasTTY() {\\n    for _, state := range sessions {\\n        if state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n            return s.addTrailerForAgentCommit(...)\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe fix should be to check for ACTIVE session first, regardless of TTY:\\n\\n```go\\n// Fast path: when an agent is committing (ACTIVE session), skip interactive prompts.\\n// The agent can't respond to TTY prompts even if a TTY is available.\\nfor _, state := range sessions {\\n    if state.Phase.IsActive() {\\n        return s.addTrailerForAgentCommit(...)\\n    }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis way, any commit during an ACTIVE session will skip interactive prompts, whether or not there's a TTY.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":10,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":661,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":117723,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":661},\"output_tokens\":4,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYGBsfCMKFWjSRuUDNEg5\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"248b13ca-48fe-4fab-ae5e-97b8a984d13c\",\"times