o can't use gemini cli due to this.\\n\\n### 4. CI Environment Detection Issue\\nThe Gemini CLI does not enter interactive mode (no prompt appears) if an environment variable starting with CI_ (e.g., CI_TOKEN) is set. This is because the is-in-ci package, used by the underlying UI framework, detects these variables and assumes a non-interactive CI environment.\\n\\n**Solution:** If the CI_ prefixed variable is not needed for the CLI to function, you can temporarily unset it for the command. e.g., `env -u CI_TOKEN gemini`\\n\\n### 5. False Positive \\\"Awaiting Input\\\" (Issue #15835)\\nDuring long-running processes, specifically the \\\"preflight\\\" check, the CLI displays the message: \\\"interactive shell awaiting input\\\" However, no user input is actually required. If the process is left alone for approximately 30 seconds, the message disappears and the preflight checks continue as expected.\\n\\n## Debugging Tips\\nUse the --debug flag for more detailed output. In interactive mode, press F12 to view the debug console.\"],\"durationSeconds\":24.76507937499974},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"0d54e940-1969-4409-9d48-eeb0df3b6ec1\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b3addf3e-b5aa-4903-b292-f2d125152570\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"4a9dde92-9a32-4a2f-ae0b-c9f6e026cd16\",\"version\":\"2.1.17\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"bright-drifting-jellyfish\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-5-20251101\",\"id\":\"msg_01UGbV9PvsMR3U9M4948Wjeh\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"This confirms that hanging on interactive prompts is a known issue with Gemini CLI. The most relevant issue is #10909 \\\"Agent hangs on interactive shell prompts\\\" which describes exactly this problem - when commands request interactive input, the agent becomes stuck.\\n\\nThe workaround suggested is to pass `-y/--force` flags where supported, but for git hooks