"filesOverlapWithContent: failed to get shadow commit, falling back to filename check\\\",\\n    68→\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()),\\n    69→\\t\\t)\\n    70→\\t\\treturn len(filesTouched) > 0\\n    71→\\t}\\n    72→\\n    73→\\tshadowTree, err := shadowCommit.Tree()\\n    74→\\tif err != nil {\\n    75→\\t\\tlogging.Debug(logCtx, \\\"filesOverlapWithContent: failed to get shadow tree, falling back to filename check\\\",\\n    76→\\t\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()),\\n    77→\\t\\t)\\n    78→\\t\\treturn len(filesTouched) > 0\\n    79→\\t}\\n    80→\\n    81→\\t// Get the parent commit tree to determine if files are modified vs newly created.\\n    82→\\t// For modified files (exist in parent), we count as overlap regardless of content\\n    83→\\t// because the user is editing the session's work.\\n    84→\\t// For newly created files (don't exist in parent), we check content to detect\\n    85→\\t// the \\\"reverted and replaced\\\" scenario where user deleted session's work and\\n    86→\\t// created something completely different.\\n    87→\\tvar parentTree *object.Tree\\n    88→\\tif headCommit.NumParents() > 0 {\\n    89→\\t\\tif parent, err := headCommit.Parent(0); err == nil {\\n    90→\\t\\t\\tif pTree, err := parent.Tree(); err == nil {\\n    91→\\t\\t\\t\\tparentTree = pTree\\n    92→\\t\\t\\t}\\n    93→\\t\\t}\\n    94→\\t}\\n    95→\\n    96→\\t// Check each file in filesTouched\\n    97→\\tfor _, filePath := range filesTouched {\\n    98→\\t\\t// Get file from HEAD tree (the committed content)\\n    99→\\t\\theadFile, err := headTree.File(filePath)\\n   100→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   101→\\t\\t\\t// File not in HEAD commit. This happens when:\\n   102→\\t\\t\\t// - The session created/modified the file but user deleted it before committing\\n   103→\\t\\t\\t// - The file was staged as a deletion (git rm)\\n   104→\\t\\t\\t// In both cases, the session's work on this file is not in the commit,\\n   105→\\t\\t\\t// so it do